Subject: Re: [T2] dumb question

Well, if you want to operate remotely from the engine compartment, the
hard one to reach is the solenoid post. If your remote starter switch
is in the engine compartment, it is easier to reach over to the
battery to complete the circuit. Some just leave it in all the time
for convenience.

John

On Wed, Mar 31, 2010 at 1:03 AM, Mike Soultanian <msoultan(-at-)csulb.edu> wrote:

> Or just connect the switch between the starter post (which has +12v coming
 to it) and the solenoid.  No need to run all the way back to the battery
 when you already have +12v at the starter.
